  <body>
    <div style="basic">
        <p begin="00:00:00.040" end="00:00:02.280" tts:direction="ltr">Hello, visitors.</p>
        <p begin="00:00:02.280" end="00:00:03.800" tts:direction="ltr">For this adventure guide,</p>
        <p begin="00:00:03.800" end="00:00:09.520" tts:direction="ltr">you're going to learn how to add analytics
<br />to your views and</p>
        <p begin="00:00:09.520" end="00:00:17.200" tts:direction="ltr">charts and uncover some additional
<br />insights by using the tools and Tableau.</p>
        <p begin="00:00:17.200" end="00:00:22.880" tts:direction="ltr">In order to do that, we're going to
<br />specifically cover trend lines,</p>
        <p begin="00:00:22.880" end="00:00:25.840" tts:direction="ltr">reference lines, reference bands,</p>
        <p begin="00:00:25.840" end="00:00:29.600" tts:direction="ltr">and some animation to show those changes
<br />over time.</p>
        <p begin="00:00:29.600" end="00:00:33.000" tts:direction="ltr">Let's dive into our file.</p>
        <p begin="00:00:33.000" end="00:00:38.155" tts:direction="ltr">You should be looking at the AG Analytics
<br />S file.</p>
        <p begin="00:00:38.155" end="00:00:43.470" tts:direction="ltr">The Tableau workbook and you should be on
<br />the overview tab.</p>
        <p begin="00:00:44.270" end="00:00:47.830" tts:direction="ltr">Let's pretend that you are in a meeting
<br />with</p>
        <p begin="00:00:47.830" end="00:00:52.270" tts:direction="ltr">your colleagues and you're the data
<br />analyst,</p>
        <p begin="00:00:52.270" end="00:00:56.830" tts:direction="ltr">and the team is trying to determine
<br />whether or not they're meeting</p>
        <p begin="00:00:56.830" end="00:01:02.870" tts:direction="ltr">the company quota or how many sales by
<br />segment compared to an overall average.</p>
        <p begin="00:01:02.870" end="00:01:07.510" tts:direction="ltr">Luckily, Tableau allows you to add
<br />reference lines, bands,</p>
        <p begin="00:01:07.510" end="00:01:11.120" tts:direction="ltr">and distributions to compare your data and
<br />the view</p>
        <p begin="00:01:11.120" end="00:01:15.960" tts:direction="ltr">very quickly and those tools are all found
<br />in the analytics pane.</p>
        <p begin="00:01:15.960" end="00:01:18.720" tts:direction="ltr">Here we have our data pane and we have all
<br />of</p>
        <p begin="00:01:18.720" end="00:01:22.360" tts:direction="ltr">our various dimensions and measures,</p>
        <p begin="00:01:22.360" end="00:01:24.880" tts:direction="ltr">and then we have the analytics pane.</p>
        <p begin="00:01:24.880" end="00:01:26.120" tts:direction="ltr">If you just select that,</p>
        <p begin="00:01:26.120" end="00:01:30.440" tts:direction="ltr">then you can begin to see some of those
<br />immediate tools like constant line,</p>
        <p begin="00:01:30.440" end="00:01:34.360" tts:direction="ltr">average line, average with 95%.</p>
        <p begin="00:01:34.360" end="00:01:37.320" tts:direction="ltr">This is we'll apply that in</p>
        <p begin="00:01:37.320" end="00:01:41.440" tts:direction="ltr">an upcoming video and then reference line
<br />and reference bands.</p>
        <p begin="00:01:41.440" end="00:01:47.230" tts:direction="ltr">So I want you to remember that when you
<br />need specific values or ranges,</p>
        <p begin="00:01:47.230" end="00:01:50.830" tts:direction="ltr">you need a continuous access on Tableau.</p>
        <p begin="00:01:50.830" end="00:01:53.870" tts:direction="ltr">While we won't use all of these features
<br />in this class,</p>
        <p begin="00:01:53.870" end="00:01:55.710" tts:direction="ltr">this is a great place to explore</p>
        <p begin="00:01:55.710" end="00:02:00.670" tts:direction="ltr">potential insights using these powerful
<br />analytic tools.</p>
        <p begin="00:02:01.790" end="00:02:06.550" tts:direction="ltr">The first one we're going to check out is
<br />the trend lines.</p>
        <p begin="00:02:06.550" end="00:02:11.950" tts:direction="ltr">We'll jump into the trend line tab on the
<br />worksheet</p>
        <p begin="00:02:11.950" end="00:02:16.240" tts:direction="ltr">and My computer is</p>
        <p begin="00:02:16.240" end="00:02:20.640" tts:direction="ltr">a little slow that I'm recording and
<br />launching Tableau at the same time.</p>
        <p begin="00:02:20.640" end="00:02:24.600" tts:direction="ltr">You might have this query processing
<br />request</p>
        <p begin="00:02:24.600" end="00:02:28.480" tts:direction="ltr">every once in a while and you should see</p>
        <p begin="00:02:28.480" end="00:02:32.400" tts:direction="ltr">on this sheet a line graph</p>
        <p begin="00:02:32.400" end="00:02:37.000" tts:direction="ltr">and it's showing the sales for gift
<br />baskets over time.</p>
        <p begin="00:02:37.000" end="00:02:41.800" tts:direction="ltr">What I'd like to do is look at the trend
<br />so I can maybe</p>
        <p begin="00:02:41.800" end="00:02:46.720" tts:direction="ltr">better understand and provide some
<br />information to my team.</p>
        <p begin="00:02:46.720" end="00:02:48.920" tts:direction="ltr">You can see this is very sporadic.</p>
        <p begin="00:02:48.920" end="00:02:50.640" tts:direction="ltr">But by adding a trend line,</p>
        <p begin="00:02:50.640" end="00:02:59.780" tts:direction="ltr">I might be able to begin to see some
<br />trends and some confidence intervals.</p>
        <p begin="00:02:59.780" end="00:03:03.860" tts:direction="ltr">What we'll do is we will go here to the
<br />analytics pane.</p>
        <p begin="00:03:03.860" end="00:03:08.180" tts:direction="ltr">It should be open, and we're going to go
<br />ahead and do a trend line.</p>
        <p begin="00:03:08.180" end="00:03:11.540" tts:direction="ltr">I'm going to just drag it and drop it.</p>
        <p begin="00:03:11.540" end="00:03:17.850" tts:direction="ltr">Now, there are Several several options for
<br />your trend line.</p>
        <p begin="00:03:17.850" end="00:03:19.890" tts:direction="ltr">You have linear, logarithmic,</p>
        <p begin="00:03:19.890" end="00:03:22.250" tts:direction="ltr">exponential, polynomial, and power.</p>
        <p begin="00:03:22.250" end="00:03:24.770" tts:direction="ltr">You can see only three of those are
<br />available.</p>
        <p begin="00:03:24.770" end="00:03:28.810" tts:direction="ltr">You will almost always be using linear.</p>
        <p begin="00:03:28.810" end="00:03:31.410" tts:direction="ltr">If you know enough about statistics to use</p>
        <p begin="00:03:31.410" end="00:03:33.890" tts:direction="ltr">exponential or polynomial, then go ahead.</p>
        <p begin="00:03:33.890" end="00:03:35.650" tts:direction="ltr">But for basic business data,</p>
        <p begin="00:03:35.650" end="00:03:38.450" tts:direction="ltr">it will almost always be linear.</p>
        <p begin="00:03:38.450" end="00:03:40.450" tts:direction="ltr">We'll go ahead and select that.</p>
        <p begin="00:03:40.450" end="00:03:42.850" tts:direction="ltr">Now you can see that trend line.</p>
        <p begin="00:03:42.850" end="00:03:44.650" tts:direction="ltr">If you hover over it,</p>
        <p begin="00:03:44.650" end="00:03:48.905" tts:direction="ltr">it gives you the R squared and the P
<br />value.</p>
        <p begin="00:03:48.905" end="00:03:55.400" tts:direction="ltr">Now, this is important because if you
<br />studied statistics,</p>
        <p begin="00:03:55.400" end="00:03:57.360" tts:direction="ltr">which I'm sure many of you have already,</p>
        <p begin="00:03:57.360" end="00:04:00.440" tts:direction="ltr">you understand that our value</p>
        <p begin="00:04:00.440" end="00:04:06.880" tts:direction="ltr">provides and explains the amount of
<br />variance within the data.</p>
        <p begin="00:04:06.880" end="00:04:11.880" tts:direction="ltr">The model that was used to draw this line
<br />or has this</p>
        <p begin="00:04:11.880" end="00:04:16.960" tts:direction="ltr">0.5 2274, our squared value.</p>
        <p begin="00:04:16.960" end="00:04:22.440" tts:direction="ltr">What that explains is that there's about a
<br />5% of variance in the data.</p>
        <p begin="00:04:22.440" end="00:04:27.345" tts:direction="ltr">Now the P value is less than 0.0 001.</p>
        <p begin="00:04:27.345" end="00:04:29.130" tts:direction="ltr">And that's very low.</p>
        <p begin="00:04:29.130" end="00:04:31.410" tts:direction="ltr">Normally for business applications,</p>
        <p begin="00:04:31.410" end="00:04:35.210" tts:direction="ltr">you would like to see that at about 0.10
<br />or below</p>
        <p begin="00:04:35.210" end="00:04:41.090" tts:direction="ltr">and the P value is the chance that a
<br />result happened randomly.</p>
        <p begin="00:04:41.090" end="00:04:43.210" tts:direction="ltr">If you're working in the scientific field,</p>
        <p begin="00:04:43.210" end="00:04:46.450" tts:direction="ltr">then a P value of 0.05 is</p>
        <p begin="00:04:46.450" end="00:04:50.810" tts:direction="ltr">preferred just due to the nature of
<br />scientific research.</p>
        <p begin="00:04:50.810" end="00:04:55.410" tts:direction="ltr">We're going to add some confidence spans
<br />to this trend line.</p>
        <p begin="00:04:55.410" end="00:04:58.425" tts:direction="ltr">If I select that, I can just hit Edit.</p>
        <p begin="00:04:58.425" end="00:05:00.520" tts:direction="ltr">The dialog box appears.</p>
        <p begin="00:05:00.520" end="00:05:02.840" tts:direction="ltr">Again, you could switch the model type
<br />here.</p>
        <p begin="00:05:02.840" end="00:05:04.480" tts:direction="ltr">You could add some factors,</p>
        <p begin="00:05:04.480" end="00:05:06.200" tts:direction="ltr">and then you have some options here.</p>
        <p begin="00:05:06.200" end="00:05:10.000" tts:direction="ltr">You can have this be shown in the tooltip,
<br />or you can remove that.</p>
        <p begin="00:05:10.000" end="00:05:13.440" tts:direction="ltr">Let's go ahead and select the show
<br />confidence bands,</p>
        <p begin="00:05:13.440" end="00:05:15.480" tts:direction="ltr">and then you can also have</p>
        <p begin="00:05:15.480" end="00:05:19.240" tts:direction="ltr">the trend line to be a different color if
<br />you add another one,</p>
        <p begin="00:05:19.240" end="00:05:21.680" tts:direction="ltr">and then show recalculated line when you</p>
        <p begin="00:05:21.680" end="00:05:24.940" tts:direction="ltr">select different areas and I'll show that
<br />in just a moment too.</p>
        <p begin="00:05:24.940" end="00:05:27.840" tts:direction="ltr">Here we've got these confidence bands</p>
        <p begin="00:05:27.840" end="00:05:32.160" tts:direction="ltr">and there are 95% confidence bands that
<br />have been added.</p>
        <p begin="00:05:32.160" end="00:05:35.120" tts:direction="ltr">These are telling you that 95% of the time</p>
        <p begin="00:05:35.120" end="00:05:39.560" tts:direction="ltr">the true average of sales falls within
<br />this range.</p>
        <p begin="00:05:39.560" end="00:05:42.640" tts:direction="ltr">What I like to do when I use the
<br />confidence band is to really</p>
        <p begin="00:05:42.640" end="00:05:46.640" tts:direction="ltr">understand if it's in the same zone, in
<br />the same direction.</p>
        <p begin="00:05:46.640" end="00:05:52.410" tts:direction="ltr">In this case, it is. I can feel fairly
<br />confident that Um,</p>
        <p begin="00:05:52.410" end="00:05:55.170" tts:direction="ltr">that sales are trending upwards.</p>
        <p begin="00:05:55.170" end="00:05:57.450" tts:direction="ltr">Although there begins because I don't have</p>
        <p begin="00:05:57.450" end="00:06:00.170" tts:direction="ltr">as much data back here in the back end,</p>
        <p begin="00:06:00.170" end="00:06:02.010" tts:direction="ltr">they begin to widen here.</p>
        <p begin="00:06:02.010" end="00:06:08.570" tts:direction="ltr">But I feel pretty confident that it would
<br />be still in an upward trajectory.</p>
        <p begin="00:06:11.060" end="00:06:20.060" tts:direction="ltr">Let's tackle reference lines next and
<br />we'll head to the reference line tab,</p>
        <p begin="00:06:20.060" end="00:06:22.140" tts:direction="ltr">the sheets, we've got two of them.</p>
        <p begin="00:06:22.140" end="00:06:27.860" tts:direction="ltr">The first one is several bar charts and</p>
        <p begin="00:06:27.860" end="00:06:30.540" tts:direction="ltr">one way that we can help aid</p>
        <p begin="00:06:30.540" end="00:06:34.260" tts:direction="ltr">our analysis is to add a reference line or
