        <p begin="00:06:34.260" end="00:06:37.260" tts:direction="ltr">These are properties of an axis.</p>
        <p begin="00:06:37.260" end="00:06:41.780" tts:direction="ltr">Just remember that reference lines are
<br />part of</p>
        <p begin="00:06:41.780" end="00:06:47.180" tts:direction="ltr">the axis because they show a value
<br />accordingly across a continuous measure.</p>
        <p begin="00:06:47.180" end="00:06:49.460" tts:direction="ltr">I'm going to create a reference lines to
<br />look at</p>
        <p begin="00:06:49.460" end="00:06:52.820" tts:direction="ltr">the average amount of sales for each of
<br />our three categories.</p>
        <p begin="00:06:52.820" end="00:06:55.940" tts:direction="ltr">Because I've got three categories and
